        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5166</citedRange> (Franz)</bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>65, 10</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#smith-porcher1864"/>, n. <citedRange>29</citedRange> (drawing)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4862</citedRange> (Blass)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, p. 34 n. <citedRange>4 B</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2180, B</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>008100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63371"><name nymRef="#Βαρκαῖος">Βαρκα<unclear>ῖ</unclear>ος</name>                    
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63309"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀστυκλῆς">Ἀστυκλεῦς</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65049"><name nymRef="#Μνάστα">Μνάστα</name>
                    <lb n="4"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64727"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Κρῖνις">Κρίνιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#mohamed-jmr1997">Βαρκα<unclear>ῖ</unclear>ος</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#pacho1827"><orig>ραρκληοσ</orig></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#CIG"><supplied reason="lost">Χ</supplied>αρ<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied>κλῆος</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#smith-porcher1864">Βαρκλῆος</rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Barkaios fils d'Astykles. Mnasta fille de Krinis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Barkaios son of Astykles. Mnasta daughter of Krinis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Barkaios figlio di Astykles. Mnasta figlia di Krinis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>باركيوس بن أستيكلوس. مناستا ابنة كرينيوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>From the same tomb, not precisely identified in the South Necropolis, come also <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086400</ref> 
                    and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086500</ref>. <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086200</ref> might also come from that tomb and is 
                    probably somewhat later.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
